        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 3:05PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 304 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Highway 138 Diamond Lake Summit, or 11 miles
northwest of Crater Lake. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph frequent lightning, and penny
size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible. Due to the nearly stationary movement of the
storm, standing water and ponding is possible on area
roads.

Locations impacted include...
Thielsen View Campground, Broken Arrow Campground, and Highway 138
Diamond Lake Summit.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
